irfechan, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Hywel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name. Some write the name Hoel, which they render 'lordly;' if so, it may come from huail, a vice-regent, regent. Arthur derives the surname Howell from Corn. -Brit, houl, the sun; and he adds, high, exalted.' But Hywel is rather from hywel, conspicuous."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Gronwy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name of uncertain derivation, borne in the <i>Mabinogi</i> by  Goronwy the Staunch , Lord of Penllyn. He became the lover of the flower-maiden Blodeuedd and murdered her husband  Lleu Llaw Gyffes , but Lleu was later restored to life and definitively dispatched Goronwy."],"variants":[{"name":"Gronw","meanings":["Variant of   Goronwy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gronwy ap Hywel was born in 1240, in Llanfairfechan, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Hywel 'Dew' ap Cadwgon, was 36 and his mother, Betyn Norris, was 30. He had at least 2 sons with Nest ferch Madog."},"et":{"year of 1240–":"1240–Surnud","1230–1300":"1230–1300","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1257–Male":"1257–Surnud","1440–Male":"1440–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1249–1329":"1249–1329","1304–1355":"1304–1355","1204–1320":"1204–1320","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","year of 1240":"1240","1440":"1440","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1304":"1304","1249":"1249","1204":"1204","1257":"1257","1235":"1235","1355":"1355","1245":"1245","1300":"1300","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1329":"1329","of Gorddinog,Llanfairfechan,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Llanfairfechan, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"year of 1240–":"1240–Kuollut","1230–1300":"1230–1300","1235–Male":"1235–Kuollut","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1245–Male":"1245–Kuollut","1257–Male":"1257–Kuollut","1440–Male":"1440–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1249–1329":"1249–1329","1304–1355":"1304–1355","1204–1320":"1204–1320","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","year of 1240":"1240","1440":"1440","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1304":"1304","1249":"1249","1204":"1204","1257":"1257","1235":"1235","1355":"1355","1245":"1245","1300":"1300","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","1329":"1329","of Gorddinog,Llanfairfechan,Caernarvonshire,Wales":"Llanfairfechan, Caernarfonshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"year of 1240–":"1240–Décédé","1230–1300":"1230–1300","1235–Male":"1235–Décédé","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","1245–Male":"1245–Décédé","1257–Male":"1257–Décédé","1440–Male":"1440–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1249–1329":"1249–1329","1304–1355":"1304–1355","1204–1320":"1204–1320","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","year of 1